<hr>
<br>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author(s). (Year of publication). <em>Title of webpage</em>. URL
</blockquote>
<br>
If content is likely to change over time, include a retrieval date before the URL. Use n.d. for 
&#8216;no date&#8217; if the publication date is not available. When the author and website name 
are different, include the website name after the title of the webpage.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author. (n.d.). <em>Title of webpage</em>. Website Name. Retrieved Month Day, Year, from URL
</blockquote>
<br>
When the author and the website name are the same, omit the website name from the reference.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author(s)">Smith, A., &amp; Brown, B.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2019</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Web page">Independent public toilet user survey</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Website Name">Tim Buck Two</span>. 
	<span class="hover fake-aref" title="URL">http://www.timbucktwo.edu/gvu/usersurveys/toiletsurvey/</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
The URL is displayed as a hyperlink. 
